profile:
Aqua Tech Waterproofing  is the most experienced and affordable privately owned company that offers basement  waterproofing,underpinning, basement lowering,concrete floors and drain services to families and businesses across the Greater Toronto Area. Based out of Toronto and operating over 20  trucks across GTA, we are conveniently located to service you in Oakville, Richmond Hill, Metro Toronto or Ajax. 

With more than 25 years of experience our trained technicians offer a quality, reliable and stress free waterproofing service. You can count on it. In addition, our friendly and professional staff is here to answer any questions you may have about our company or our services. 

Have an emergency? Don’t hesitate. Our 24 hour Emergency phone line is here to serve you better.

Clogged drains? Leaking taps? Clogged toilet? Repairs? and more? We have what you need at highly competitive prices you can afford. We will either match or even beat other estimates. At Aqua Tech Waterproofing and Drain, our goal is about doing the job right the first time around.

We use the most sophisticated technology combined with high knowledge of our services, which means the problem is fixed fast by a systems qualified plumber, leaving you worry free.

We look forward to hearing from you.

Award Winning Specialists!
416-236-8721

A&A Masonry is an award-winning Toronto based firm specializing in almost everything exterior.  Specialties include Stone work, Interlock, Interlocking, Paver stones, paving stones, Natural Stone, Pavers, Stone Veneer Cladding, Tuckpointing, Masonry, brick repair, brick restoration, tuck pointing, waterproofing, foundation repairs, concrete steps, porches, walkways, caulking services (windows & doors), chimney repair and general exterior restorations for residential, commercial and industrial customers.

A&A is dedicated to providing the highest quality on every job. With a proud team of qualified artisans, we strive to complete every project in a timely and safe manner.

Our mission is to offer a unique and reliable service in anything Exterior within the Greater Toronto Area, differentiating ourselves from the competition by means of always delivering what we promise, on time and on budget.

Our commitment to excellence is our core value.
Customer satisfaction is our main goal, and we reach it every day by relying on our attention to customer service. By providing customized solutions for every job, we guarantee that we will never compromise on quality, safety and efficiency.

profile:
Three Little Pigs Masonry provides expert masonry and concrete repairs, restoration and installation for the home and business owner.  
Our estimating department works as a team to find long term solutions and  help homeowners with many permanent solutions to their problems where other competitors have failed to succeed. Having over 45 years experience doesn't hurt either. 
The team at Three Little Pigs Masonry works together to provide the customer with a positive contractor experience from the first call to the last team member to leave your completed project. Most importantly,  you are dealing with actual MASONS from the management, the estimators and the crews on your property. 
No sales person will call and no high pressure sales pitch. Our warranties reflect the confidence Three Little Pigs Masonry provides.
Compare our warranties to those of our competitors. 
We are a family owned and operated business that prides itself  on the highest quality work and  providing exceptional customer service.

We specialize in STONE REFACING , structural masonry and concrete including underpinning and walk outs!

profile:
Thank you for taking the time to visit our Homestars page!

We appreciate any opportunity to provide a free quote for your wet basement waterproofing and foundation crack repair. Dryshield is a Family owned and operated basement waterproofing company Toronto and most of southern Ontario. We pride ourselves on our basement waterproofing and foundation crack repair workmanship. Our mission is to continue providing you with the highest quality products, technologies and procedures at the most competitive price for your wet basement waterproofing needs.  We offer a wide range of solutions for your leaky or wet basement. Some of the solutions are; internal drainage systems, external waterproofing, window wells, basement crack repair and sump pumps.  

All of our work provided is Dryshield employed and not by subcontractors.  Our team at Dryshield works hard day in and day out to provide you with the highest quality of workmanship. 

We are fully licensed and insured. All prices are up front with no hidden surprises. Dryshield can beat any quality competitor with a difference in cost and quality.

Things to look for that can be contributing to your wet basement:

-	Are your down spouts discharging at the side of your house or are they connected to the ground?
-	Is the grade sloping towards your house causing a wet basement? 
-	Do you see any signs of a foundation concrete crack? 
-	How old is your home is and what condition are your weeping tiles are in?


If you have a wet basement and need a waterproofing company for your basement waterproofing needs contact Dryshield today!

www.waterproofingservice.com or 1-800-277-5411

profile:
Welcome to Canada Waterproofers, your one stop shop for all your waterproofing, plumbing and drain repair needs. Canada Waterproofers provide top-quality material and service. With over 25 years experience we know what products, methods and application works best for your unique situation.

Canada Waterproofers specialize in helping you with all your Waterproofing Drain and Plumbing needs. For 25 years servicing the local community with pride.

We believe that high quality workmanship and materials are key to get he job done right the first time. Canada Waterproofers treat our customers homes as if it was our own. From complete home waterproofing to minor repairs…we do it right!

Canada Waterproofers believes in old school values, this is very important in a business filled with dishonesty and careless workmanship.

Here at Canada Waterproofers we are proud of our work, and love to share every step of the job with our customers. Doing this they can understand and be involved on how the job being performed and applies to their unique situation. 

Canada Waterproofers can help you with any project big or small, and are always just a phone call away to answer any questions or concerns. 

We believe in personalization so when you call our company we won’t send you a sales person. We believe that this is unfair to our customers as we are not interested in just selling a job, but rather figuring out what the problem is at your home and offering the best solution.

Benefits to our customers


25 Year Transferable warranty provided
Over 25-years experience in the industry.
We are fully licensed, insured and have full WSIB coverage
Highly trained technicians that are licensed plumbers and waterproofers.
Building renovators licenses.
Underpinning experts.
We will detect any water leakage on your property, and fix it the first time!
Free non- obligation estimate is provided to all costumers. 
We use the latest technology available to make sure our services are top quality.
We only repair what is required, at very competitive prices. Saving homeowners thousands of dollars.

Integrity, Honesty and the highest quality workmanship within the industry. Canada Waterproofers is here for you. 

Canada Waterproofers will provide a free no obligation written quote before any work is performed. Once you decide to go ahead with the work rest assured one of our technicians will be constantly monitoring the onsite site activity to be sure that the work is performed to our high standards. 

Our technicians pride themselves attending to the smallest of details. Nothing is left to chance therefore ensuring your project is completed to the highest standards.

Here are just some services that we provide

Exterior waterproofing
Interior waterproofing
Sump pump installations
Sump pump battery back up systems
Backflow preventers 
Snaking
Camera inspections
Plumbing
And more...

The Team at Canada Waterproofers will only be content when our customers are happy. It’s important our company constantly keeps up our high quality in workmanship and materials to be sure that our customers are completely satisfied now and in the future.

The climate is changing and the challenge of keeping our aging homes becomes more of an issue. Canada Waterproofers are up for the task. Your basement will stay dry and your plumbing will perform properly for years to come. Choose Canada Waterproofers.

profile:
DrainWorks Plumbing is a customer-first, Toronto-based plumbing company providing full plumbing services, drain cleaning, drain repair and drain replacement. All our plumbers are 100% licensed, insured and commission-free! We take great pride in being one of the most reviewed companies on HomeStars in North America! We are also proud to say that we have been chosen (twice) as the "best plumber in the city" by Toronto Life magazine, as evidenced by their "Busy person's survival guide" issue. High praise from a wonderful and trusted publication! 

We employ full-time salaried plumbers rather than commission-based plumbers that are motivated to up-sell you. All of the DrainWorks plumbers in Toronto and surrounding areas are fully licensed, insured, and professionally trained. We are also proud to say that 100% of our employees have been with us for 10 years or more. Finally, an experienced local plumber near you that you can trust and rely on!
 
Further, we've recently had the honor of being one of a select few companies across all trades, hand picked by Gemini award winning TV host and contractor, Bryan Baeumler, of HGTV's Leave it to Bryan and Disaster DIY to be Baeumler Approved. A high mark of quality, indeed. 
 
You can count on DrainWorks for all your plumbing and drain-related needs in Toronto. Our plumbers are ready for your call with clear and upfront pricing and will always arrive on-time and fully prepared with everything they can foreseeably need.

DrainWorks Plumbing also likes to help and support our local Toronto community and charities, such as for the Easter Seals and SickKids Foundation.
Please take a few moments to read these plumbing reviews from our customers, so you too can learn about and take advantage of the ‘DrainWorks Difference’. We hope you choose us for your next call to the plumber!

At Tornado Plumbing we work hard to fulfill all your plumbing needs, and offer some of the best service in the GTA. Our products are high quality, and all of our work is under warranty. We provide free estimates, competitive rates, and city rebates are available.
Our services include waterproofing, pipe burst, plumbing repairs, backwater valve, concrete work, water service and repairs, drain camera inspections, drain snaking, and underpinning (basement lowering).
With appointments booked at your convenience, and 24 hour emergency service, you’re sure to get the job done with Tornado Plumbing.

services:
Waterproofing
Our skilled crews take all the necessary steps to clean and prepare your foundation wall prior to waterproofing.
We only use materials of the highest industry standard to seal your home from leaks.
With a 25 year warranty, you are guaranteed a dry basement and piece of mind.

Drains
When you need to replace your damaged sewer lines, we meet all city standards for drain work and backwater valves.
Using the minimally invasive pipe burst method, we can have your drains running again quickly.

Water Service
Using trench-less technology we can quickly replace your lead waterline or
upgrade your current water service, causing minimal damage to your property

Plumbing
We can take care of all your plumbing needs no matter the size.
Fixing small leaks to full plumbing line replacement, and everything in between.

Concrete work
From walkways to patio slabs we’ve got all your concrete needs covered.

Underpinning & Walkouts
If you’re looking for more living space, we can lower your basement to your desired height or add a second entrance.
Using approved engineer drawings, and following building codes, we will create the basement you want.

24/7 EMERGENCY SERVICE

profile:
WATERPROOFING

Tired of mopping the water in your basement? Does your basement smell of mould and mildew? Is your foundation wall retaining water slowly and deteriorating? If the answer is yes to any of these questions, then the following will describe the reasons why, and how, to eliminate the problem. The cause of your basement's musty smell is because your foundation wall is retaining water, be it in the hollow block cavities or trapped behind the double brick or stone wall, as well as the water that is absorbed by the block, brick and stone. This combination causes the wall to produce mould, mildew and epharecense. The water trapped in the wall slowly deteriorates the wall, starting at the bottom.The water that makes its way into the basement through the wall and seems to cause us the most grief may not be the most concerning problem. The same problem will not occur with a solid poured concrete wall. The reason being you will find a defined crack in the solid wall that allows all the water to enter in, without retaining little, or any water.Regardless of which type of foundation you have, it can become watertight, mould and mildew-free by sealing your foundation from the OUTSIDE. With solid poured concrete foundations, you can inject the crack from the inside and the elements stay out.You must expose your foundation wall from grade level to 6" below the top of the footing. Then you must clean the wall thoroughly, exposing the deteriorated areas and cleaning all the dust and dirt from the wall. Then, restore any cracks or loose mortar joints with hydrolic cement. Cement coat the wall,Tar and install 6mm poly plastic on top. Once the wall is treated, install a 4" continuous weeping tile covered with 6 inches of 3/4" stone. Then back-fill the earth compacting at every foot. At grade level slope the earth, concrete, interlocking etc. away from the house.This method never fails. I have used this system over 13 years without fail. I have the references for you to refer to. We also have a photo album to take you step by step through the procedure.So, stop mopping! Relieve your allergies from mold and mildew and restore your foundation. When you do decide to restore your foundation do it the right way - from the outside. Remember, 40% of all my work is fixing other people's attempt to stop the water.

No more unattended drainage problem resulting in slow running drains especially in the kitchen, laundry and bathrooms. Snaking is often successful but hydro jetting could be the answer to remove oil and grease settled in the drain.

products:
High grade polyurethane injection resin. A single component, hydrophobic product which is designed for sealing leaks through cracks, rock pockets and expansion joints in concrete structures. This resin and accelerator mixture reacts when it comes into contact with water and forms a micro cellular closed cell gasket with excellent adhesion and long-term flexibility.
The cured hydrophobic compression gasket that is formed in the joint or crack remains stable and is highly resistant to degradation resulting from repeated freeze/thaw and wet/dry cycles.

SAFE. Tested and classified by UL in accordance with Standard ANSI/NSF61 for contact with potable water. 100% solids and harmless to the environments. Also, no unpleasant odors.
services:
-Free Written Estimates
-Locate problem area if unknown or if area is finished.
-Protect and prep area for repair.
-Remove finished areas/obstructions to gain access to the problem.
-Waterproofing crack/hole/joint through high pressure injection using high grade polyurethane.
-Full clean up after job completion.
-Provide 25 year transferable warranty certificate.
specialities:
Repairs can be completed all year round and during any type of weather condition.
*OUR REPAIR PROCESS DOES NOT WORK WITH BLOCK/STONE FOUNDATIONS. Only poured concrete foundations. Homes after 1968.

profile:
A to Z Plumbing and Drain's specialty is installation of sump pumps and backwater valves, basement waterproofing,  professional video camera inspection and repairs to your water, drain and sewage system at a reasonable, competitive price. I am Dmitry Monastirsky, certified and licensed Master Plumber, and the owner of the company. I invite you to check our reviews, and call us with your plumbing issue. A former engineer, I find solutions to complex plumbing problems that other plumbers either walk away from, or end up quoting you too much. 

As clients of A to Z Plumbing and Drain often note, I take the burden of paperwork and permits off their shoulders, saving them  frustration and time. Every member of my crew is experienced and efficient. They come on time, do superb job, and leave your home clean. 

We get  lifelong clients  by being honest, clean, punctual, and doing quality work for a reasonable price.  We spend time solving your problem, not bashing our competition. We use new technologies such as pipe burst technology to do the job efficiently, and pass the savings on to you. Our goal is to provide excellent service for our clients. 
Are you skeptical about our average 10 out of 10 stars reviews? Some people think it is unattainable, but we are the living proof that it is possible.  We get them by doing an excellent job, by over-delivering quality for a competitive price for each and every client.  
Among hundreds of Toronto certified plumbers, we stand out by giving you our unconditional guarantee.

We guarantee that you get:

- $20 off your repairs if our plumber is not on time at your door

- One to 25 years warranty for the work we do in your home

- Clean service – Your carpets and floors stay as clean as they were before we arrived

- Honest pricing – we charge by the job, not by hour, and we do not charge mileage. Our prices are reasonable.

- Job done right the first time – We work fast and so that no rework is ever needed.

Please check our reviews, and give us a call!

profile:
Waterproofing, Foundation Repair, Underpinning, Concrete Specialties

Our Construction Services

Waterproofing

We have all heard the horror stories. It’s spring. The snow is melting, the rain is heavy and the basement floods.  The reasons for a wet, or even damp, basement, can be many.  Heavier rainy seasons and milder winters are causing the ground to freeze and thaw several times before spring. This contributes to constant shifts in the ground and wrecks havoc on cracked or weak foundations. As torrential rain downpours become more commonplace, these compromised foundations simply cannot keep the water out.    more about wet basements  ....

Regardless of the reason for a home’s wet basement, Aquashield Waterproofing will assess each issue and identify the most suitable solution to fix the problem(s).  more about Aquashield’s specific waterproofing techniques ...

Check out our Video! (attention dial-up users: LARGE file 7.5MB)
Foundation Repair

There are many different ways to repair foundations depending on the type of foundation, the source of the problem and the level of damage.  In many cases, the foundation wall can be repaired with relatively simple and straight-forward techniques.  Depending upon the specifics of the issue and the accessibility of the problem area, repairs can be completed from either the outside or the inside of the residence.

In extreme cases, homeowners may need to consult with a structural engineer to confirm whether a home’s foundation is sound or if the foundation may need to be rebuilt.  In other cases, another foundation wall built next to the original will provide the necessary reinforcement.

Each waterproofing and foundation repair company will have its own preferred methods.  Typically, however, the solution is simple. Some companies, however, will sell homeowners on extremely expensive methods, technology and materials.  At Aquashield Waterproofing we will not complicate things unnecessarily. We will work hard to identify the most effective and cost-efficient solution for your home’s foundation issues.  more about foundations & their problems ...
Underpinning

When a basement requires more ceiling height or the foundation needs to be strengthened and stabilized, both can be achieved through underpinning.  This process involves carefully digging out small sections of the ground below the existing foundation wall in a 1-2-3 sequence that will add depth and stability. To ensure continued support for the structure, it is not safe to underpin an entire length of a wall in one go. The work must be done in sections. A small section, below and beside the existing foundation is excavated and temporary supports may be installed to support the main weight-bearing walls during this process.

The excavated sections are then filled with concrete to create a new foundation or series of concrete footings beneath the original.  This process of underpinning is an effective method to extend the depth and width of support offered by the  original foundation. Once the foundation wall is lowered, a new concrete floor can be poured, providing additional height in a basement.
Concrete Specialties

Walkouts, driveways and more

In addition to waterproofing and foundation repair, Aquashield Waterproofing’s services extend to a variety of specialty concrete projects, including basement walkouts, driveways and parging.

profile:
Although dealing with the obvious surface issues such as downpipes, eavestrough's, window wells, grading etc., are the first steps recommended and the ones which are most commonly used, these only mask the symptoms temporarily rather than dealing with the root of the problem. Common sense dictates that you never want water ponding or pooling on the surface against the outside walls, but if it did, it shouldn't end up in your basement. If water or excessive dampness is entering through your basement foundation walls or at the footing level, then you have a serious foundation problem. Foundation waterproofing and restoration of your walls below grade with the installation of a new weeping tile system is really your only proper and long-term solution.

Please remember that unlike in previous generations, basements are now being used as living space rather than just storage or utility space. Basements have become an integral part of homes as they provide much needed and relatively affordable living space unlike additions, which can be cost prohibitive. Therefore, steps need to be taken in order to protect your basement environment as you would the upper floors of your home, should it have a leaky roof. Keep in mind, foundations are what support a house and are vital to its structural integrity.

Unfortunately they have long been neglected, as it was accepted that the basement was a dark, gloomy and musty place. Fortunately, with today's innovative building materials and advanced waterproofing systems, Watertite can offer homeowners a dry basement that will protect your existing finished space or allow you to safely create new living space such as a playroom, office or recreation room without the fear that your new finishes will be water damaged and potentially ruined by mould. Waterproofing your home will give you piece of mind knowing that you have a dry, healthy, livable basement area and at the same time you have extended the longevity and integrity of your foundation walls for many years to come.
 
Call Watertite for a free consultation before you decide to finish your basement area or if you are experiencing any of the symptoms as outlined in our Do I have a problem section, within your existing finished basement.
 
Advantages To Waterproofing
 
    * Dry and leak free basements
    * Reduced overall dampness
    * Help reduce the risk of mould growth
    * Creates a healthier basement environment
    * Protects the structural integrity of the foundation
    * Allows you to confidently renovate, refinish or repair your  basement
    * Creates equity in your home and facilitates resale
    * Includes a fully written Lifetime transferable warranty

profile:
OUR COMPANY VALUES
Quality. Integrity. Value.
 

The Inside Guys are a full-service basement improvement company, with an emphasis on basement lowering, waterproofing and underpinning. Having worked in the industry for the past 26 years, on over 250 projects within the GTA for various construction companies, we noticed that there was something missing with some of these bigger companies: the communication and professionalism was lacking on many jobsites.

We decided to model our company based on higher ethical standards combined with superior craftsmanship. We realize that we are only as good as our last job and future work success is dependent on our reputation. We not only want to exceed your expectations for the work but also how smooth the project runs so we pride ourselves on being there from the day one until it’s done.
We care about what we build for you.


WE DO ALL THE WORK.



We work with every client, one-on-one from start to finish. We promise to not only quote the work, but to also do the work.

This is something unique in our industry – we want to bring back accountability to the jobsite and ensure homeowners are treated with knowledge and respect.

From the moment we take on your project, your peace of mind is our main priority. We want a clear and transparent process, with on-going communication and continuous support so you can be assured the job will get done right the first time.


We will not only promise to do all of the day to day work but we will also act as project supervisors and ensure that each project is constructed to plan with no variations. We will deal with the City of Toronto Inspectors directly so that no communication is lost if there are ever any discrepancies.
If you have any questions at the end of the day we will provide you with pictures of the day’s work and let you know what the next steps will be.


At the end of the day, it comes down to trust. We feel that we must earn it.

At the end of each job you will receive a folder that includes the original drawings, locates, inspection reports and a zip drive of images for your peace of mind.

Uncompromising quality, exceptional service, competitive pricing and unsurpassed results.

profile:
Welcome to Toronto Drains & Waterproofing! Our services are backed by a 100% satisfaction guarantee. Contact us today to schedule your appointment. 

Camera Inspections

Cutting edge camera equipment with location services
All pipe sizes between 2-10 inches no matter the style of piping (clay, PVC, ABS, cast iron, copper)
Continuous drain backups – we utilize a camera to pinpoint any and all issues in your drainage system

Drain Replacement 

Underground Drain Replacement and Repairs
Removal of older damaged piping causing backups and damage to the home
Trenchless technology for piping replacements (pipe bursting)
Installation of backwater valves
Spot repairs, up to full line replacements



Backed Up and Clogged Drains

We will fully repair the cause of the following symptoms, at their source:
Basement main drain backing up with sewage spilling out of the floor drains onto your finished and unfinished basements
Water backups out of sink drains
(Temporary) water pools around shower drain
Toilet bowl water bubbles when running the sink or shower
Slow draining of water from your bathtub, sink or other fixture (can indicate a clog, even if a backup hasn’t yet been exposed)
Gurgling sounds from drains, especially after running washing machine or dishwasher
Any mysterious puddles of water on floor near a tub, sink or floor drain


Wet Basements

Installation of basement flood protection device such as a Backwater valve or sump pump system
Exterior waterproofing with the installation of new weeping system
Interior waterproofing
Sump pits and pumps
We will also fully repair the cause of the following symptoms, at their source:
Water seeping through your foundation walls (may rise up through the floors)
Heavy rains or flash floods causing you to have a wet and mouldy basement
name: Toronto Drains & Waterproofing.

profile:
At Dry Worx Waterproofing, we believe strongly in honesty, ethics and integrity. We will not offer an estimate on or undertake any project unless we are perfectly clear what the problem is and how it can be repaired. We will not try to up sell a job beyond the scope of your needs. We will stand behind all our work 100% with a written lifetime transferable warranty. We will provide a full refund if after 3 repair attempts (initial repair + 2 warranties) the leak persists and the homeowner declines any more warranty work. We will perform all repairs in a timely workmanlike manner according to all standard building codes and practices. We will show full respect to your family, home and property while performing our duties.

Our goal is to ensure your home remains permanently free from leaks that damage your home and belongings. These leaks if left unchecked can develop into serious mould and air quality issues which can affect your family’s health and lower the value of your home. We are experts in all aspects of basement waterproofing and are industry leaders; our highly qualified technicians will use only the most advanced foundation repair methods and materials available. Whether repaired from the inside or the outside you can count on Dry Worx Waterproofing to do the job right the first time, on time, every time, for the price quoted. Our knowledge of the industry and confidence in our technicians allows us to provide a written lifetime transferable warranty and money back guarantee. If we do not stop the leak you receive a full refund, it is as simple as that. Ask any other companies if they are that confident. Then call us. We offer free estimates, flexible evening and weekend appointments and a 10% discount for seniors. For basement waterproofing that works Call 1-877-DRY-WORX.

profile:
"NOBODY BEATS OUR PRICES!" PLUS 25 Year Transferable Warranty! Basement waterproofing for residential home owners or commercial business owners helps to maintain or increase property values. Water leaks and drainage problems in walls and floors decrease property values; hence, the price of prevention and of minor repairs is a smart investment by owners in their properties. Whether it is exterior excavating to repair leaking foundation block walls or poured concrete or interior waterproofing of walls, floors and crawl spaces for example, the work must be done to prevent and/or stop water leaks, seepage, condensation and dampness.

    If waterproofing work performed by contractors is not done when necessary, using an interior sump pump system and/or exterior sealants, primers, tar, epoxy, caulk, membrane materials such as dimple board, Blue Skin, gravel and weeping tiles, below grade, below bricks and masonry, then—at worst--flooding may eventually occur. If not eventual flooding, then at the least there will be a gradual deterioration of concrete, brick and mortar until costly restoration repairs become necessary in order to prevent further water damage to walls and floors. Water damage will decrease property values.

    Overtime as water drops become constant leaks or ever-present seepage, causing condensation and dampness, this problem can lead to mildew, musty smells and moulds that can cause mild to severe health problems. Whether the leaks are originating from under the yard, the lawn, the driveway asphalt or concrete, or from foundation wall cracks, holes, gaps or pipe penetrations, then basement waterproofing by Basement Leaks Fixed is the best solution because it comes with a twenty-five year transferable warranty! Our work and our Transferable Guarantee not only provides piece of mind for the home or business owner because it solves water and/or drainage problems, but it also insures that an owner’s property values are maintained and improved.

profile:
Our main goal is to give you the foundation for a dry home through the installation of waterproofing solutions that are tailored to your unique situation. For decades, homeowners have been able to rely on the innovative solutions from Basement Waterproofing and Draining Solution which include everything from crawlspace and basement waterproofing to foundation repairs.

Our solutions continue to outlive lifetime warranties by at least three times. We have a professionally trained team of sales representatives in the Ontario area to assess and give a quote on basement waterproofing, foundation repairs or any needed draining solution. All our installers are employees of BWD, most of whom have a long term working relationship of more than 25 years. We also carry full insurance which include HST registration and WSIB coverage.
​
Waterproofing technology continues to evolve year after year. The technology our company used when we first opened our doors has changed completely. To keep up with the times, our team is constantly looking for better ways to improve our services and we always embraced the best and latest technology in the industry. We work with some of the leading manufacturers of waterproofing materials in order to foster the latest innovations in the industry.
​
With our knowledge and experience, you can be confident knowing you are working with the best service providers in the market. Your comfort is our responsibility and we are good at what we do. Contact us today and let us help you reclaim your comfort.

To schedule a Free-No-Obligation inspection with us, please contact our local headquarter located in Mississauga, Ontario, Canada. Our contact page has all the details on how to get in touch with us.
